    &lt;CommentText&gt;Good afternoon,  
thank you for taking the time to post this story, following your recent appointment. This does not sound like you were treated with the dignity and respect which we would expect from any member of Trust staff and I am very sorry for the clear distress this caused you.  
Based on your description of these recent events, it may be possible for me to identify you from speaking with clinic staff and relay this feedback to the individual Doctor and their supervisor. However, if you would like to discuss this with a member of my team in more detail and receive some feedback following this, the PALS and Complaints Team are able to assist and support you. They can be contacted on 0161 922 4466, or via email [palsandcomplaints@tgh.nhs.uk](mailto:palsandcomplaints@tgh.nhs.uk).  
Once again, please accept my apologies that you were left feeling this way following your appointments and assurances that should we not be able to identify the Doctor, this feedback has been shared with the Directorate Manager for Pain Services for her to share with the whole Team.  
Kind regards, Alex&lt;/CommentText&gt;
